			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Hello all,
<br />

<br />
My guild has been restricting pet casters from using pets on several encounters where mobs are believed to spawn each time a player or pet dies.  Examples like <a href="http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=8561" target="_blank" class="postlink">Shei Vinitras</a> in Akheva, and <a href="http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=10359" target="_blank" class="postlink">Rallos Zek The Warlord</a> in Fortress of Zek.  Players leave corpses when they die, pet's don't.  So perhaps pets don't cause adds.  But then again, I'm not sure if the spawned adds are related to just any death in general, or just player deaths.
<br />

<br />
Last night this bit us badly, as we only had 55 people at Rallos Zek, and all the pet casters were told to go petless.  Our kite-team did a pretty good job grabbing the spawned-mobs and kiting them away from the raid, BUT we did not have the DPS to tear down Rallos Zek in time.
<br />

<br />
Also, I use Epic pet on tons of encounters for the exact reason I have stated many times on this board.  Epic pet's high aggro allows me, and every damage dealer out of melee range to lay on much higher DPS because the pet provides an aggro wall.  If the top of the hate list is within a mob's melee range, that mob will stay put then hit the highest PLAYER on melee range.  Not only did my raid lose DPS with no pets, but we lost the ability to do as much damage with no Epic pet.  In fact, even though I was putting a good 15 seconds average between casts of Sun Vortex, I still got summoned and killed at RZWL = 35%.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">I have two big questions for those of you who are really experienced at Rallos Zek The Warlord and other mobs that spawn adds when players die.</span>
<br />

<br />
#1.  Do pet deaths really cause adds to spawn just like players?  
<br />

<br />
