			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Istaril,
<br />

<br />
I'm familiar with the aggro-jump from taunt theory, but I'm not yet sure if I have bought into it.  I seem to remember many times in the past where I can generate huge aggro on a mob, and run around while a tank follows the mob and taunts.  In those cases, I don't remember a time when my aggro was very high and the tank pulled the mob off me within a few taunts.
<br />

<br />
Anyways, IF the aggro-jump theory is correct, then that means the Epic pet still helps the main tank generate aggro.  Because the pet would be generating aggro at it's normal rate while the main tank still gets to hold the mob on himself.  Then the main tank would be constantly jumping his aggro value to just above the pet.  In this case, if the pet died the warrior would grab top aggro very soon, which is better in fact and even MORE reason to use Epic pet.
<br />

<br />
Yeah, I realize water pet from behind is our highest DPS pet.  The point I am making with Epic pet, is me going from Epic to Water is a gain of like 25 DPS on a mob like Rallos Zek.  But me using Epic pet when my main tanks aggro is low, could up the DPS of the ENTIRE RAID.  So which has more value, more DPS from 1 pet, or more DPS from a raid full of damage dealers?
<br />

<br />
My guild is 3 months old.  We went from no keys/flags to Vex Thal Keyed and flagged for Elemental Planes in 3 months.  Some of our members are pretty well equipped, some are very new.  We have 2 warriors in the guild that can tank pretty well and hold good aggro.  I'm not sure either of them  can surpass Epic pet on aggro generation though.  Every time I use Epic pet I notice our kills happen with less overaggro deaths.  I'm sure there will be a point in the future where the main tank can out aggro Epic pet.  It's just not yet.<br />_________________<br /><Center><b><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=36994" target="_blank" class="postlink">Sage Eandori Raintree</a></b>
<br />
<a href="http://www.eqempyreal.com" target="_blank" class="postlink">Empyreal</a> - Solusek Ro Server</b>
<br />
<span style="font-style: italic"><a href="http://forum.magecompendium.com/viewtopic.php?t=13760" target="_blank" class="postlink">"The pinnacle of pet offensive power can be achieved at level 50 with the epic pet. Does this make sense?"</a></span>
<br />
</center></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
